        "messages": {
          "values": [
            {
              "content": "=Act as a Senior SDET (Software Development Engineer in Test). Your goal is to perform a root-cause analysis on the provided Jest failure log.\n\n====================\nINPUT DATA\n====================\nRaw Test Log: \n{{ $('Webhook').item.json.body.rawLog }}\n\n====================\nDIAGNOSTIC TASKS\n====================\n1. CLASSIFICATION: Categorize the failure into one of these three:\n   - REGRESSION: A logic bug. The code changed, but the test wasn't updated or the code is now incorrect.\n   - BRITTLE: Environment/Flaky. Look for keywords like \"timeout\", \"ECONNREFUSED\", or \"MongooseServerSelectionError\".\n   - SYNTAX/MOCK: The test file itself has an error, such as a missing import or an invalid Jest mock.\n\n2. TRACE MAPPING:\n   - Identify the specific file path and line number of the failure.\n   - Identify which 'describe' or 'it' block failed.\n\n3. LOGIC SUMMARY:\n   - Provide a \"Expected vs. Received\" comparison in plain English.\n   - Explain the \"Root Cause\" in one simple sentence.\n\n====================\nSTRICT OUTPUT FORMAT\n====================\nReturn ONLY the following Markdown structure:\n\n### 🔍 Failure Diagnosis\n- **Classification:** [Regression | Brittle | Syntax]\n- **Location:** `File:Line`\n- **The \"Why\":** [1-sentence explanation]\n- **Recommended Action:** [What the developer should do next]"
            }
          ]
        },
        "builtInTools": {},
        "options": {}
      },
